AFRICA Cup of Nations giant-killers Comoros faces a goalkeeping crisis before the biggest game in the country’s history on Monday. The tournament debutants play hosts and five-time champions Cameroon in Yaounde on Monday, but their camp has been hit by 12 positive Covid cases including coach Amir Abdou. Read Also: Ramat Cup kicks off February 12   COVID-19 rules Tunisia coach, 12 players out of Eagles tie     CAF names Eguavoen best coach     Ramat Cup kicks off February 12   Seven players have been affected, including the two remaining fit keepers in the squad, Moyadh Ousseini, and Ali Ahamada, with first-choice Salim Ben Boina out through injury. “We will do everything in our power to find a solution,” said general manager El Hadad Himidi. - Advertisement - Himidi added: “It’s the coach and the only fit goalkeepers, so the situation is really complicated.”